ah-nah-KON-dah or AH-noh-KOHN-dah

===Etymology===
: From the [[Sinhalese]] ''[[henakandaya]]'' (meaning "one with large body"), a species of (now extinct) constrictor found in [[Sri Lanka]]

===Noun===
'''anaconda''' (plural anacondas)

# Any of various large [[nonvenomous]] [[snake]]s of the genus ''[[Eunectes]]'', found mainly in northern [[South America]].  Their length can grow to as much as 5 m (15 ft).

